ble%20minority%20communities%20in%20Bangladesh.%20The%20recent%20surge%20in%20violence%20against%20Hindu%20communities%20poses%20an%20urgent%20and%20alarming%20threat%20to%20peace%20and%20stability%20in%20the%20region%2C%20and%20the%20time%20to%20act%20is%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20organizers%20passionately%20called%20for%20immediate%20protection%20and%20safety%20for%20all%20religious%20minorities%20in%20Bangladesh%2C%20urging%20the%20US%20government%20to%20refuse%20to%20remain%20a%20silent%20bystander%20as%20these%20heinous%20crimes%20against%20humanity%20unfold.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20encouraged%20Bangladeshi%20Hindus%20to%20stay%20vigilant%20and%20unite%20in%20monitoring%20the%20ongoing%20situation%2C%20taking%20necessary%20initiatives%20collectively%20in%20any%20emergency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20vigil%2C%20aptly%20titled%20%26quot%3BSave%20Hindus%20in%20Bangladesh%2C%26quot%3B%20was%20organized%20by%20the%20Global%20Voice%20for%20Bangladesh%20Minorities%2C%20an%20umbrella%20organization%20representing%20major%20Houston%20Hindu%20groups%2C%20including%20Maitri%2C%20Vishwa%20Hindu%20Parishad%20of%20America%2C%20HinduAction%2C%20HinduPact%2C%20Houston%20Durgabari%20Society%2C%20ISKCON%2C%20Global%20Kashmiri%20Pandit%20Diaspora%2C%20and%20many%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EParticipants%20raised%20their%20placards%20high%2C%20bearing%20passionate%20messages%20demanding%20an%20end%20to%20the%20violence%20and%20atrocities%20against%20Hindus%20in%20Bangladesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20crowd%20erupted%20with%20fervour%20as%20slogans%20like%20%26quot%3BStop%20Hindu%20Genocide%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BStand%20Up%20and%20Speak%20Out%20Now%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BHindu%20Lives%20Matter%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BWe0%20Won't%20Run%2C%20We%20Won't%20Hide%2C%20Stop%20Hindu%20Genocide%26quot%3B%20rang%20out%2C%20echoing%20their%20urgent%20plea%20for%20justice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EQuoting%20the%20timeless%20words%20of%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%2C%20%26quot%3BTo%20forgiv