ntent%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Simone%20Biles%2C%20Rebeca%20Andrade%2C%20and%20Jordan%20Chiles%20take%20a%20selfie%20together%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20Women's%20Floor%20Exercise%20Final%20at%20the%20Olympic%20Games%20Paris%202024.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66b8bbadb4912df3ae1a96a9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESimone%20Biles%2C%20Rebeca%20Andrade%2C%20and%20Jordan%20Chiles%20with%20their%20medals.%3Cp%3EEurasia%20Sport%20Images%2F%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EJordan%20Chiles%20has%20to%20return%20her%20bronze%20medal%20after%20the%20Court%20of%20Arbitration%20for%20Sport%20stepped%20in.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EChiles%20had%20been%20elevated%20to%20third%20in%20the%20floor%20exercise%20following%20her%20coach's%20appeal%20over%20her%20score.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20the%20court%20voided%20the%20on-floor%20appeal.%20The%20IOC%20has%20confirmed%20the%20ruling.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparis-olympics-breakout-athletes-on-social-media-data-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egymnast%3C%2Fa%3E%20Jordan%20Chiles%20will%20be%20required%20to%20give%20back%20the%20bronze%20medal%20she%20won%20in%20the%20floor%20exercise%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Folympics%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EParis%20Olympics%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tas-cas.org%2Ffileadmin%2Fuser_upload%2FCAS_Media_Release_ParisOG_15-16.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edecision%20by%20the%20Court%20of%20Arbitration%20for%20Sport%20(CAS)%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChiles%20had%20finished%20the%20event%20in%20fifth%20with%20a%20score%20of%2013.666.%20But%20after%20an%20on-floor%20appeal%20by%20her%20coach%20over%20her%20difficulty%20score%2C%20officials%20lifted%20her%20rating%20by%200.1%20to%2013.766%2C%20elevating%20her%20into%20third%20place%20ahead%20of%20Ana%20B%C4%83rbosu%20%E2%80%94%20after%20the%20Romanian%20athlete%20had%20already%20begun%20celebrating.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EB%C4%83rbosu%20was%20visibly%20distraught%20after%20looking%20at%20the%20scoreboard%20and%20realizing%20what%20had%20happened.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20CAS%20has%20now%20determined%20that%20Chiles'%20coach's%20appeal%20was%20filed%20four%20seconds%20outside%20of%20the%20one-minute%20window%20allowed%20by%20the%20International%20Gymnastics%20Federation%20(FIG)%2C%20and%20her%20initial%20score%20of%2013.666%20was%20reinstated%20%E2%80%94%20putting%20B%C4%83rbosu%20back%20in%20third%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20International%20Olympic%20Committee%20(IOC)%20confirmed%20the%20ruling%20on%20Sunday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20IOC%20will%20reallocate%20the%20bronze%20medal%20to%20Ana%20Barbosu%20(Romania).%20We%20are%20in%20touch%20with%20the%20NOC%20of%20Romania%20to%20discuss%20the%20reallocation%20ceremony%20and%20with%20USOPC%20regarding%20the%20return%20of%20the%20bronze%20medal%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20IOC%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrazil's%20Rebeca%20Andrade%20won%20gold%20in%20the%20event%2C%20with%20Team%20USA%20star%20Simone%20Biles%20taking%20silver.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUSA%20Gymnastics%20and%20the%20US%20Olympic%20%26amp%3B%20Paralympic%20Committee%20(USOPC)%20released%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fusagym.org%2Fjoint-statement-from-usa-gymnastics-and-the-u-s-olympic-paralympic-committee-regarding-the-cas-decision-on-the-womens-floor-final%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejoint%20statement%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20the%20decision%2C%20saying%3A%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20devastated%20by%20the%20Court%20of%20Arbitration%20for%20Sport%20ruling%20regarding%20women's%20floor%20exercise.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20inquiry%20into%20the%20Difficulty%20Value%20of%20Jordan%20Chiles'%20floor%20exercise%20routine%20was%20filed%20in%20good%20faith%20and%2C%20we%20believed%2C%20in%20accordance%20with%20FIG%20rules%20to%20ensure%20accurate%20scoring%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20statement%20continued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20USOPC%20has%20said%20it%20will%20appeal%20the%20CAS%20ruling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUSA%20Gymnastics%2C%20in%20a%20separate%20Sunday%20statement%20posted%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fusagym%2Fp%2FC-itH1bJiB8%2F%3Figsh%3Dd2hydXU4ZTJocnBn%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInstagram%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20indicated%20it%20had%20submitted%20a%20letter%20with%20video%20evidence%20to%20CAS%20%26quot%3Bconclusively%20establishing%20that%20Head%20Coach%20Cecile%20Landi's%20request%20to%20file%20an%20inquiry%20was%20submitted%2047%20seconds%20after%20the%20publishing%20of%20the%20score%2C%20within%20the%201-minute%20deadline%20required%20by%20FIG%20rule.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20letter%2C%20USA%20Gymnastics%20requests%20that%20the%20CAS%20ruling%20be%20revised%20and%20Chiles'%20bronze-medal%20score%20of%2013.766%20be%20reinstated%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20statement%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20USA%20Gymnastics%20and%20USOPC%20statement%20also%20said%20that%20Chiles%20had%20faced%20%26quot%3Bextremely%20hurtful%20attacks%20on%20social%20media%26quot%3B%20since%20the%20incident%20occurred.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNo%20athlete%20should%20be%20subject%20to%20such%20treatment.%20We%20condemn%20the%20attacks%20and%20those%20who%20engage%2C%20support%2C%20or%20instigate%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20Instagram%20Story%20on%20Saturday%2C%20Chiles%20said%20that%20she%20was%20stepping%20away%20from%20social%20media%20for%20her%20mental%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Folympics.com%2Fioc%2Fnews%2Ften-olympians-from-three-editions-of-the-olympic-games-awarded-their-olympic-medals-during-reallocation-ceremony-at-paris-2024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Internati